[[File:Giovanni_Paolo_Pannini_-_Charles_III_at_St_Peter%27s_-_WGA16967.jpg|thumb|350px]]
'''''Charles of Bourbon Visiting [[St Peter's Basilica]]''''' is a painting by [[Giovanni Paolo Pannini]], commissioned by its subject [[Charles III of Spain|Charles of Bourbon]] in 1746 and completed later that year. It was part of the same commission as the same artist's ''[[Charles of Bourbon Visiting Pope Benedict XIV at the Coffee House del Quirinale]]'' and both works are now in the [[National Museum of Capodimonte]] in Naples.

==Bibliography==
